USA: Repetition is the Mother of Wisdom
It is comic that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan issue the strategy of his predecessor, whom he himself took for the dumbest.
When he finally revealed his Afghan approach, expected with anxieties, it was demonstrated that it is a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only does the same text use several times the "equal as in Iraq", but he also did not hesitate to use the title of the Bush statement of January 2007 for his own statement: "A new path forward".
It was himself, who three years ago criticized Bush's idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from the civil war. And that criticized him as "an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences".
In the next few months, however, they demonstrated that Bush's strategy, based on the recommendations of field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that today nothing is spoken of Iraq in the news.
Bush's reputation did not improve, however objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than was expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama expects the miracle to be repeated.
The field captains again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially the commander-in-chief of the Afghan General Operation Stanley McCristal. He, even despite the traditional subordinate relations, subjected the undecided gunmen to harsh criticism in the White House.
He asked for 40,000 men to be able to improve the situation.
The president hesitated for three months, but he didn't think of anything better, so at least he cheated on the general over 10,000 military.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he had previously had at least 10,000.
The most problematic thing about Obama's entire strategy seems to be his goal, starting to withdraw Afghan troops in 18 months and finish this procedure in three years. Obama's entire doctrine generated more questions from the answers he offered.
Many doubt that the increase will bear the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratriced wars in recent years, Iraq's society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: no one can be trusted and no agreement is reached.
Under these conditions it is difficult to prepare the Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing the boss each day according to their needs.
The political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a people of Potemkin. After it will remain the patriarchal tribal relations.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extremely complicated due to confusing relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capable of action", a minimum objective of the entire operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama's strategy is shocked by his voluntarism.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to worsen and is now about to explode.
Only a romantic soul, who doesn't know anything about reality, can believe that the soldiers sent to war to "come home soon," will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, setting the date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of U.S. defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that Europeans are less and less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their electors, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with the Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to worsen and the increased sanctions do not have any effect on Iranians, the US will have to make a difficult decision: to try to resolve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to seek the answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphal withdrawal of Afghanistan's troops.
However, each solution in this way will mean a dramatic setback to the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that it is three years away for the presidential elections and that is why there is still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if it is a total failure.
